definitions.definition: To pass a slower moving object or entity (on the side closest to oncoming traffic).
examples: The racehorse overtook the lead pack on the last turn.
The car was so slow we were overtaken by a bus.

definitions.definition: To become greater than something else in quantity, worth, etc.
examples: Grocery sales in the north have overtaken those in the south.

definitions.definition: To take by surprise ; surprise and overcome ; carry away .
examples: Our plans were overtaken by events.

main_definition: To pass a slower moving object or entity (on the side closest to oncoming traffic).
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To become greater than something else in quantity, worth, etc.
To take by surprise ; surprise and overcome ; carry away .
